name: IN THE GARDEN
description:
High-quality giclee print of the artwork "In The Garden".
The original piece was created using graphite pencil, acrylic and watercolour on paper.

This print is available in A4 size.
Hand signed and titled on back.

Using a combination of dye-based and pigment-based inks to achieve weather-resistant vivid colours on archival papers, these prints are designed to last. When displayed unprotected with a bare bulb, these colour prints will last up to 25 years, at least 50 years framed under glass, and well over 75 years framed under glass with UV protection. Black and white prints can last up to 100 years under glass.

The print method uses over 7500 nozzles to achieve an accurate and highly detailed replica of the original artwork without pixilation. Meanwhile the 300gsm archival papers are made of 100% cotton and are designed specifically for museum displays. This high quality stock has an exceptional tonal range and an extra smooth matte finish.

All prints are packaged securely inside a cello sleeve and with a backing board.
